INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('73', '1', '2013-04-23 13:44:16', '2013-04-23 13:44:16', '<div>\r\n\r\nCity Park is a 170-acre mixed use community located in southwest Charlotte. It is a pedestrian-friendly, fully integrated development designed to accommodate 2,500 residential units, 200,000 SF of retail space, 400,000 SF of office space and 350 hotel rooms. City Park’s accessible location and natural amenities distinguish it from any other mixed use development in Charlotte.\r\n<h3 style=\"display: inline !important;\">CITY PARK IS SURROUNDED BY:</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More than 5 million square feet of office space (the second largest concentration of office space in North Carolina)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A 140-acre park featuring mountain bike trails, tennis courts, baseball and soccer fields and a 18-hole golf course</li>\r\n	<li>More than 50,000 passengers per day at The Charlotte Douglas International Airport</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 style=\"font-size: 13px;\">TRAFFIC COUNTS (NCDOT 2011):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>21,000 vehicles/day on Tyvola Road at City Park Drive</li>\r\n	<li>29,000 vehicles/day on Billy Graham Parkway southeast of Tyvola Road</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 style=\"font-size: 13px;\">RECREATION:</h4>\r\nThe City Park brand is recreation. The target market is a technologically savvy, recreationally minded, highly mobile, 24 - 35 year-old demo- graphic. City Park features miles of sidewalks, acres of green space, pedestrian connectivity\r\nand a quality of life enhanced by the recreational amenities in and around City Park.\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 1.17em;\">CITY PARK’S HIGHLY ACCESSIBLE LOCATION IS:</span></h4>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 1em;\">Within walking distance to:</span></h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_97\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"231\"]<a href=\"http://smileg.com/2013/citypark/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/City-Park-15-minute-drive-time-pg-1-2-24-09-19.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-97\" alt=\"Drive Time Demographics For City Park Charlotte\" src=\"http://smileg.com/2013/citypark/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/City-Park-15-minute-drive-time-pg-1-2-24-09-19-231x300.jpg\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" /></a> Drive Time Demographics For City Park Charlotte[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Office</li>\r\n	<li>FarmersMarket</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p style=\"display: inline !important;\">RenaissancePark</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p style=\"display: inline !important;\">Hotels</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<p style=\"display: inline !important;\">GolfCourse</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>Less than 10 minutes from:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Interstate485</li>\r\n	<li>Interstate77</li>\r\n	<li>Interstate85</li>\r\n	<li>Charlotte Douglas International Airport</li>\r\n	<li>Light Rail Line</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Less than 15 minutes from:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>SouthPark</li>\r\n	<li>MyersPark</li>\r\n	<li>Uptown</li>\r\n	<li>LakeWylie</li>\r\n	<li>Dilworth / South End</li>\r\n	<li>U.S. National Whitewater Park</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 1em;\">Demographics</span></h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_99\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"231\"]<a href=\"http://smileg.com/2013/citypark/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/City-Park-Primary-Residential-Demographics-pg1-2-24-09-15.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-99\" alt=\"City Park - Primary Residential Demographics\" src=\"http://smileg.com/2013/citypark/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/City-Park-Primary-Residential-Demographics-pg1-2-24-09-15-231x300.jpg\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" /></a> City Park - Primary Residential Demographics[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 1em;\">Important Links</span></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.cms.k12.nc.us/Pages/Default.aspx\" target=\"_